{{Infobox language |name=Djimini |nativename= |states=[[Ivory Coast]] |region=[[Dabakala Department]] |ethnicity=[[Djimini people]] |speakers={{sigfig|95,500|2}} |date=1993 |ref=e18 |familycolor=Niger-Congo |fam2=[[Atlantic–Congo languages|Atlantic–Congo]] |fam3=[[Senufo languages|Senufo]] |fam4=[[Tagwana–Djimini languages|Tagwana–Djimini]] |iso3=dyi |glotto=djim1235 |glottorefname=Djimini Senoufo }}
'''Djimini''' (Jinmini) is a southern [[Senufo languages|Senufo]] of [[Ivory Coast]]. Blacksmiths among the Djimini once spoke [[Tonjon language|Tonjon]], a [[Mande language]].
