'''Idakho''', '''Isukha''', and '''Tirikhi''' (''Luidakho, Luisukha, Lutirichi'') are mutually intelligible Kenyan languages within the Luhya ethnic group. They are a set of languages closely related to some other Luhya ethnic groups like [[Maragoli]], but less so in comparison to others, like [[Bukusu]]. ==References== <references/>
