'''Giuseppe''' "'''Joseph'''" '''Ida''' (born November 6, 1890, [[Calabria]], [[Italy]]) was the head of the [[Philadelphia Mafia]] during the 1940s and 1950s, following the death of [[Giuseppe Dovi]] in 1946. Ida retired and returned to Italy in 1959, leaving the title of [[Boss (crime)|boss]] of the Philadelphia crime family to [[Angelo Bruno]].<ref name="Capeci2012">{{cite book|last=Capeci|first=Jerry|title=The Complete Idiot's Guide to the Mafia, 2nd Edition|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=o64XJkmUPr0C&pg=PA74|accessdate=6 February 2013|date=2012-01-10|publisher=Penguin|isbn=9781440625824|pages=74–}}</ref><ref name="Nash2010">{{cite book|last=Nash|first=Arthur|title=New York City Gangland|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ZRpNSW9zgeQC&pg=PA95|accessdate=6 February 2013|date=2010-07-28|publisher=Arcadia Publishing|isbn=9780738573144|pages=95–}}</ref>

