[[Iran]] uses three official calendar systems, including the [[Solar Hijri calendar]] as the main and national calendar, the [[Gregorian calendar]] for international events and Christian holidays, and the [[Islamic calendar]] ([[Lunar calendar]]) for Islamic holidays.
The surfeit of public holidays has been a subject of concern for almost 30 years. A substantial number of unofficial holidays are added each year to the national holidays that further aggravate the situation.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.iran-daily.com/1387/3267/html/national.htm |title=Iran Daily - National - 11/11/08 |accessdate=2017-06-17 |deadurl=bot: unknown |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090515001536/http://www.iran-daily.com/1387/3267/html/national.htm |archivedate=May 15, 2009 |df= }}</ref>
Iran has the most public holidays in the world with around 25 holidays. The holidays in Iran may differ regarding the Arabic Calendar.[http://publicholidays.me/iran/][http://www.qppstudio.net/publicholidays2016/iran.htm]
