'''Santiago "Pucho" Villalba Mederos''' (born June 5, 1991)<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://areacontrol.news/santiago-villalba-mederos/|title=SANTIAGO VILLALBA MEDEROS|date=2016-11-01|work=Area Control News|access-date=2018-08-31|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.cbsnews.com/pictures/interpols-most-wanted-americans/48/|title=Interpol's most wanted Americans|date=2018-05-31|access-date=2018-08-31|language=en}}</ref> is an American criminal who was added to the [[FBI Ten Most Wanted Fugitives]] list on September 25, 2017.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fbi.gov/news/stories/new-top-ten-fugitive-santiago-villalba-mederos|title=New Top Ten Fugitive|website=Federal Bureau of Investigation|language=en-us|access-date=2018-08-31}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.businessinsider.com/fbi-10-most-wanted-criminals-list-2017-11|title=These are the fugitives on the FBI's 10 Most Wanted list — and how they got there|work=Business Insider|access-date=2018-09-03}}</ref>

==Background==
Mederos is an alleged murderer and gang member from the state of [[Washington (state)|Washington]], and was just a teenager when he allegedly killed and wounded multiple bystanders on different occasions in Washington in 2010.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.fbi.gov/wanted/topten/santiago-mederos|title=SANTIAGO VILLALBA MEDEROS|website=Federal Bureau of Investigation|language=en-us|access-date=2018-08-31}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.cbsnews.com/news/santiago-villalba-mederos-accused-in-2-slayings-added-to-fbis-most-wanted-list/|title=Santiago Villalba Mederos, accused in 2 slayings, added to FBI's "Most Wanted" list|access-date=2018-08-31|language=en}}</ref> 

He is accused of killing  Camille Love, the injuring of her brother, and the killing of Saul Lucas-Alfonso, all were shot.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cbsnews.com/news/santiago-villalba-mederos-accused-in-2-slayings-added-to-fbis-most-wanted-list/|title=Santiago Villalba Mederos, accused in 2 slayings, added to FBI's "Most Wanted" list|publisher=|accessdate=3 September 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.seattletimes.com/seattle-news/crime/tacoma-fugitive-accused-of-2-murders-added-to-fbis-ten-most-wanted-list/|title=Tacoma fugitive accused of 2 murders added to FBI’s Ten Most Wanted list|date=26 September 2017|publisher=|accessdate=3 September 2018}}</ref> 

A reward of $20,000 has been offered for information that leads to the arrest and extradition.<ref name="theyucatantimes.com">{{cite web|url=http://www.theyucatantimes.com/2017/05/reward-offered-in-search-for-fugitive-who-may-be-in-mexico/|title=Reward offered in search for fugitive who may be in Mexico|date=19 May 2017|publisher=|accessdate=3 September 2018}}</ref> He is a member of the Eastside Lokotes Sureno (ELS) gang.<ref name="theyucatantimes.com"/>
Mederos is described as Hispanic, 5 feet 10 and 140 pounds, with black hair and brown eyes. He has a tattoo of the letter “S” on his left shoulder and the letter “E” on his right shoulder.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thenewstribune.com/news/local/crime/article175323776.html|title=Tacoma man added to FBI’s 10 Most Wanted|publisher=|accessdate=4 October 2018}}</ref>

